
@startuml
' Class Diagram for Film Set System

class Employee {
  - name: String
  - socialSecurityNumber: String
}

class CreativeEmployee <|-- Employee
class Director <|-- CreativeEmployee
class Actor <|-- CreativeEmployee

class Technician <|-- Employee {
  - fieldOfActivity: String
}

class FilmSet {
  - location: String
}

class Film {
  - title: String
  - releaseYear: Integer
  - genre: String (enum: thriller, action, horror, comedy)
}

class Screenwriter {
  - name: String
  - mostSuccessfulFilm: String
}

class Screenplay {
  - title: String
  - version: String
  - date: Date
  - numberOfScenes: Integer
  - plot: String
  - sourceType: String (enum: novel, concept)
  - sourceTitle: String
  - sourceAuthor: String (if novel)
}

class Novel {
  - title: String
  - author: String
}

class Concept {
  - title: String
}

class OscarWinner {
  - hasOscar: Boolean
}

Director <|-- OscarWinner
Actor <|-- OscarWinner

Employee "1" *-- "0..*" Film: worksOn
CreativeEmployee "1" *-- "0..*" Film: directs or actsIn
Director "1" --> "1" Film: directs
Actor "1" --> "*" Film: actsIn
Technician "1" --> "*" Film: worksOn

Screenwriter "1" --> "*" Screenplay: writes
Screenplay "1" --> "1" Film: usedFor
Screenplay "1" --> "1" Novel: basedOn (optional)
Screenplay "1" --> "1" Concept: basedOn (optional)

Film "1" --> "1" FilmSet: uses
@enduml

### Explanation of Key Relationships:
- `Employee` is the base class for all people involved in the system.
- `CreativeEmployee` is a subclass of `Employee`, which includes `Director` and `Actor`.
- `Technician` is also a subclass of `Employee`, but with a different role.
- `OscarWinner` is an interface or abstract class that both `Director` and `Actor` can implement to indicate if they have won an Oscar.
- `Screenwriter` creates one or more `Screenplay`s.
- Each `Screenplay` belongs to exactly one `Film`, and each `Film` may use multiple `FilmSet`s.
- A `Screenplay` can be based on either a `Novel` or a `Concept`.

